&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Toradex makes embedded computing modules that power products across industrial automation, medical devices, robotics, and beyond. We&#39;re looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Device Software Lead&lt;/strong&gt; who can do something harder than writing great embedded Linux code: &lt;em&gt;make the entire platform easier for others to build on&lt;/em&gt;, while keeping it robust, secure, and maintainable long-term.&lt;br&gt;You&#39;ll own the architectural direction of our device software platform, lead a team of embedded engineers, and work directly with customers and product teams to understand where the platform needs to go next. Your biggest impact will be in the decisions you make, the clarity you bring, and the engineers you grow.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role asks you to hold two things at once:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architectural clarity&lt;/strong&gt; — knowing how to draw the right boundaries between BSPs, Yocto layers, reference images, and platform features so the system stays maintainable as it scales.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customer judgment&lt;/strong&gt; — understanding how a real engineer at a customer company experiences your platform, where they get stuck, and what would unlock the next stage of their product.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;If you&#39;ve spent your career entirely heads-down in the build system, this probably isn&#39;t the right fit. If you&#39;ve found yourself drawn to &lt;em&gt;why&lt;/em&gt; the platform is structured the way it is, and how it could work better for the people using it — keep reading.&lt;/div&gt;
