&lt;li&gt;Supplier quality assurance and control (including statistical process control SPC)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting supplier audits (mostly contract manufacturers/EMS)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nonconformity and CAPA handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuous improvements of our products and processes (Lean Six Sigma, DfX, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support in customer audits and quality questionnaire answering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support improving our QMS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 years experience as a Quality Engineer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep electronics background (ideally coming from hardware development)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good electronic manufacturing process knowledge (PCB manufacturing and assembly processes (e.g. IPC-A-610)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Insight in non-destructive and destructive electronics manufacturing analysis procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Very pragmatic yet systematic approach to reach the quality objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good understanding of ISO9001:2015&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Happy to use newer tools and technologies, e.g. Jira/Confluence, AI&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluent English -&amp;nbsp; level C1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nice to have: German level B2+&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we offer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An agile and inter-cultural work environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with lastest IoT computer technology in an international environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participation in defining processes and your working environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contemporary employment conditions, modern office space and a flexible working environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunities for your personal development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
